  "description": "I first heard this species' distinctive song and was taken aback for this elevation/county. It was singing repeatedly (recording submitted). It eventually came closer where I could obtain excellent views and photos (included). Distinctive white eye with bright yellows \"spectacles\", green crown, fading into gray nape and side of neck, back green, two bright wing bars, yellow flank with white underside from chin to lower abdomen.\u00a0I believe this i a first Teller County record.",
